{"id":4,"parent_id":0,"book_id":22563,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":4,"title":"The Promised Messiah","subtitle":"","short_title":2,"uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah","content":[["div",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.head1"},[".titleNumber","2"],["h1","The Promised Messiah"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Theme"],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p4"},"Jesus was chosen from before the foundation of the world to be the Christ, the Anointed One, and his coming was heralded by all the prophets from the beginning."]],[".topic",["h2","Theme Analysis"],["div",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.f1"},["ul.content-list alphaCaps",["li",["span.label","A."],["div",[".para","Jesus was the firstborn spirit child of our eternal parents; and because he was like God in the pre-earth world, he was chosen as the Savior."]]],["li",["span.label","B."],["div",[".para","Acting under the Father’s direction, Jesus was the great Creator of the world, and he is the God of the Old Testament."]]],["li",["span.label","C."],["div",[".para","All the prophets of all the ages have identified the coming of Christ, the promised Messiah, as the greatest event of all time."]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Study Sources"],[".topic",["h3","New Testament Reading Assignment"],["div",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p11"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.1-18"},"Luke 1:1-18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/1.1-18"},"John 1:1-18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/17.1-5"},"John 17:1-5"]]],[".topic",["h3","Course Manual"],["div",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p13"},"Chapter 2, “The Promised Messiah”"]],[".topic",["h3","Standard Works"],["div",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p15"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/17.3-5,24"},"John 17:3-5, 24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/6.38,51-58"},"6:38, 51-58"],". In what way does Jesus testify of his premortal existence?"],["div",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/1.1,2,14"},"John 1:1, 2, 14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/col/1.14,15"},"Colossians 1:14, 15"],". What further information do these references give concerning the Savior’s pre-earth life?"],["div",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p17"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/13.8"},"Revelation 13:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-pet/1.18-20"},"1 Peter 1:18-20"],". Jesus was the Lamb of God, slain from before the foundation of the world.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/1.1-9"},"Hebrews 1:1-9"],". Who is the Anointed One, who was foreordained from the beginning and called a God?"],["div",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/abr/3.22-26"},"Abraham 3:22-26"],". Who was like unto God?"],["div",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p19"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/1.3,10"},"John 1:3, 10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.31-35"},"Moses 1:31-35"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.30"},"7:30"],". How vast are the creations of the Savior?"],["div",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/3.1-16"},"Exodus 3:1-16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/6.1-3"},"6:1-3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/8.56-59"},"John 8:56-59"],". What is the significance of these passages as they relate to the godhood of Jesus?"],["div",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p21"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/10.1-10"},"1 Corinthians 10:1-10"],". Who was the God of ancient Israel?"],["div",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/10.4,5"},"1 Nephi 10:4, 5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.4-10"},"Mosiah 3:4-10"],". Were the prophets specific in their predictions of the promised Messiah?"],["div",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p23"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.9-11"},"Jacob 7:9-11"],". How many of the prophets have testified of the coming of Christ?"]],[".topic",["h3","Basic Library"],["div",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p25"},["span.emphasis","A of F,"],"pp. 465-73. Jesus, the firstborn of God, was and is Jehovah."],["div",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p26"},["span.emphasis","Teachings,"],"p. 181. Jesus appointed as Savior of the world."],["div",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p27"},["span.emphasis","DS,"],"1:18-37. An overview of gospel doctrine about the Savior."],["div",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p28"},"Bruce R. McConkie in",[".address","CR,"],"Apr. 1972, pp. 133-35. A powerful testimony of the position and importance of Christ."],["div",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p29"},["span.emphasis","Jesus the Christ,"],"pp. 6-16. The premortal existence of Christ."]],[".topic",["h3","Additional Sources"],["div",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p31"},"Marion G. Romney, “Jesus Christ: Lord of the Universe,”",["span.emphasis","Improvement Era,"],"Nov. 1968, pp. 46-49."],["div",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p32"},["span.emphasis","Ensign"],"(front inside cover), Dec. 1973. This scriptural study of the many names of the Savior gives a grand overview of his all-inclusive mission"]],[".topic",["h3","Media Suggestions"],["div",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p34"},"Transparency, The Son of God Was Creator of All Things"]]],[".topic",["h2","Some Suggestions for Presentation"],[".subtitle","(Ideas Other Teachers Have Used)"],[".topic",["h3","Blackboard Presentation and Discussion"],["div",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p38"},"The teacher may wish to place a large picture of the Savior on the board with the scripture",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/17.3"},"John 17:3"],", and then ask this question: Why is it so important to know the truth about Jesus? Following this, three main columns could be drawn under the picture as follows. A discussion of the scriptures with the students could be helpful. (The scriptures given are only a sampling, and the teacher may wish to add to or change them.)"],["div",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.f2"},["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/17.3"},"John 17:3"]],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Jesus’ Premortal Foreordination"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Jesus, God of the Old Testament"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Emmanuel-God with Us"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/1.1-9"},"Hebrews 1:1-9"]],[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/abr/3.24-27"},"Abraham 3:24-27"]],[".para","Others"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/10.1-9"},"1 Corinthians 10: 1-9"]],[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/6.1-3"},"Exodus 6:1-3"]],[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/8.56-59"},"John 8:56-59"]],[".para","Others"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.23"},"Matthew 1:23"]],[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.25-27"},"Matthew 8:25-27"]],[".para","Others"]]]]]],["div",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p53"},"As we study the New Testament whom do we really learn about? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.27-31"},"John 20:27-31"],".)"]],[".topic",["h3","Scripture and Transparency Exercise"],["div",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/the-promised-messiah.p55"},"Using the overhead transparencies (1, 2, 3, ) included in the media kit, the teacher might develop an interesting discussion of the role of the Savior as Creator. The teacher could have the students ponder",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.31-33"},"Moses 1:31-33"],"; then he could show and discuss transparencies 20, 32, and . (A review of President J. Reuben Clark’s talk “Who Is This Man That We Worship?” in section 1 of the course manual may also be appropriate.)"]]]]],"refs":null}
